    <div class="row">
      <div class="image right" id="flows"></div>
      <div class="copy  left">
        <p class="small"><span class="dropcap">C</span>oinciding with the launch of their next generation consumer products, 3D Systems approached The Artificial to assist in creating a design that could be rolled out to the connected software.</p>
        <p>We began by designing an application with a focused interaction model and minimal UI elements for managing the Cube printer. Knowing that this would be a new experience for many users, we focused on creating simple task-oriented paths and clear feedback from the printing process.</p>
      </div>
    </div>      
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="image left" id="ecosystem"></div>
      <div class="copy bg-tulip right">
        <p class="medium serif">We carried the design language we'd established with the Cube printer to the hand-held 3D Sense scanner. To make the simple and linear flow shine, we showcased specific moments where the 3D Systems algorithms performed their magic.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="image right" id="details"></div>
      <div class="copy left">
        <p class="small"><span class="dropcap">D</span>etails had to be designed for all screens, from tablets to on-printer displays. We kept this range in mind as we developed out the icons and other controls, making sure the final manifestation would pixel perfect on any device.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  
    <div class="row">
      <div class="image left" id="layers"></div>
      <div class="copy right">
        <p class="gigantic condensed text-tulip">Making complicated simple</p>
        <p class="small">We worked to keep the applications simple and focused. We used simple spatial metaphors and models to keep the robust functionality and complex controls within the user's mental model.</p>
      </div>
    </div>    
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="image right" id="guidelines"></div>
      <div class="copy bg-tulip left">
        <p class="gigantic condensed">Consistency across products and platforms</p>
        <p class="small">To accommodate the growing ecosystem of tools and services, we created a visual and interaction system which would remain consistent for the user, while easily extending to include new products across consumer and professional lines.</p>
      </div>
    </div>        
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="image left" id="screens"></div>
      <div class="copy right">
        <p class="medium serif">Most recently, we've worked with 3D Systems to create their first touch interface for a line of SLS and SLA printers. We worked in an iterative process with machine operators and developers to perfect the interface for high-volume professional use.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
